1
00:00:05,968 --> 00:00:09,033
[Boy]
It's been a classic pitchers'
duel with Cole McKay,

2
00:00:09,033 --> 00:00:10,834
the team's closer,

3
00:00:10,834 --> 00:00:12,667
digging himself
out of a hole.

4
00:00:12,667 --> 00:00:15,133
Working the edges
of the plate.

5
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:18,467
It's the bottom of the ninth,
two out,

6
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:21,067
the winning run
threatening on third.

7
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,300
And the pitch.

8
00:00:29,467 --> 00:00:31,367
Swing and a miss.

9
00:00:31,367 --> 00:00:33,033
The count now 3-2.

10
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:36,400
Grady pounds his bat
on the plate in frustration.

11
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:52,367
[horn honks]

12
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:59,267
[bell tolling]

13
00:02:05,801 --> 00:02:08,701
Let's have a look.

14
00:02:08,701 --> 00:02:10,968
All right.
You look fine.

15
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,901
[door opens]

16
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,901
[bell tolling]

17
00:02:17,901 --> 00:02:20,400
[chattering]

18
00:02:32,234 --> 00:02:34,868
Get rid of the gum.

19
00:02:34,868 --> 00:02:36,634
Swallow it.

20
00:02:37,734 --> 00:02:39,434
[swallows hard]

21
00:02:39,434 --> 00:02:41,534
Don't get
your mother upset.

22
00:02:43,934 --> 00:02:45,100
[sniffling]

23
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:47,501
What's with Kathleen?
We barely even knew her.

24
00:02:47,501 --> 00:02:49,434
There's absolutely
nothing wrong with her.

25
00:02:51,133 --> 00:02:53,334
She loved to sing.

26
00:02:56,734 --> 00:02:59,000
Go keep an eye
on your brother.

27
00:03:05,234 --> 00:03:08,033
I'm sorry for your loss.

28
00:03:10,801 --> 00:03:12,968
Me and Anthony
are going to a party
later on.

29
00:03:12,968 --> 00:03:15,167
You wanna come?
Save it, Terry. Not now.

30
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:16,934
Yeah, whatever.
Like she's gonna hear us.

31
00:03:18,067 --> 00:03:20,067
She looks really good,
considering--

32
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:22,567
This old bat looks better now
than when she was alive.

33
00:03:22,567 --> 00:03:24,901
[scoffs]

34
00:03:24,901 --> 00:03:27,334
How much would you pay me
if I give her a kiss?

35
00:03:29,234 --> 00:03:31,033
T-Terry, not now.

36
00:03:31,033 --> 00:03:34,100
She's got a piece of snot
hanging out of her
right nostril.

37
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:36,300
You think that's real,
or you think they
stuck that in there?

38
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:38,334
Cut it out.
This is Dad's sister.

39
00:03:38,334 --> 00:03:41,400
So what? She never
said two words to me

40
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,901
or to the old man.

41
00:03:42,901 --> 00:03:44,334
All right.
Well, forget that now.

42
00:03:44,334 --> 00:03:47,400
She's dead,
so just say a prayer
or something.

43
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,968
I don't know any.

44
00:03:48,968 --> 00:03:52,934
Eight years of Catholic school,
and you don't know one prayer?

45
00:03:52,934 --> 00:03:56,501
Bless us, our Father,
for these, thy gifts
we are about to receive--

46
00:03:56,501 --> 00:03:59,367
Not that. I'll do it.
I'll do it.

47
00:04:01,701 --> 00:04:03,634
I'll be out
in the car.

48
00:04:03,634 --> 00:04:05,834
[Cole] Thy kingdom come,
thy will be done--
[door opens]

49
00:04:05,834 --> 00:04:08,300
on earth--
[muttering]
[door closes]

50
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,868
Lead us not
into temptation--

51
00:04:09,868 --> 00:04:13,033
Lead us <i>snot</i>
into temptation.

52
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:14,601
Thank you.
[chuckling]

53
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
What are you doing, bro?

54
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,968
What's it look like?

55
00:04:24,968 --> 00:04:27,100
Coming with us
or what?

56
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,467
Where to?

57
00:04:28,467 --> 00:04:30,667
I already told you.
To a party, remember?

58
00:04:30,667 --> 00:04:32,968
Someone invited
the two of you to a party?

59
00:04:32,968 --> 00:04:34,801
[chuckling]
[scoffs]
Forget about it.

60
00:04:34,801 --> 00:04:37,601
We don't need
no pure alter boy
hanging with us.

61
00:04:37,601 --> 00:04:39,467
Pure as your mother.

62
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:41,300
Have you even seen
a girl yet, huh?

63
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:42,801
Look, forget it.

64
00:04:42,801 --> 00:04:45,367
I just thought
since you never get out--

65
00:04:52,367 --> 00:04:55,000
He coming or what?
We got him.

66
00:04:56,701 --> 00:04:57,968
[rabbit cage opens]

67
00:04:57,968 --> 00:05:00,400
Guys, wait up.

68
00:05:14,167 --> 00:05:16,868
It's the O'Leary family.
They went to the Cape.

69
00:05:16,868 --> 00:05:19,200
Big deal, right?
[chuckling]

70
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,701
I thought we were
going to a party.

71
00:05:20,701 --> 00:05:23,501
[whispering]
Shut up!
What are you guys doing?

72
00:05:23,501 --> 00:05:25,067
[dog barking]

73
00:05:28,467 --> 00:05:30,267
I'll hold your coat.

74
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:32,267
You're out of your minds.
Don't puss out on us.

75
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:34,167
You're the only one
who can squeeze through.

76
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:39,667
No, forget it.
I'm not doing this.

77
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:41,767
Quit dicking around
and do as I say.

78
00:05:41,767 --> 00:05:44,701
Get off of me!
Trying to say something, huh?

79
00:05:44,701 --> 00:05:46,567
I can't hear you.

80
00:05:46,567 --> 00:05:50,133
The only thing I hear is,
"Okay, Terry, I'll do it."

81
00:05:52,767 --> 00:05:54,434
You're both assholes.

82
00:05:54,434 --> 00:05:56,968
We lower you in,
you go upstairs

83
00:05:56,968 --> 00:06:00,167
and you open the door,
okay?

84
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,200
Okay?

85
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:13,601
Bingo!

86
00:06:13,601 --> 00:06:16,567
[clock chiming]

87
00:06:18,234 --> 00:06:20,267
Come on.

88
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:22,067
Come on!

89
00:06:43,434 --> 00:06:45,667
Come on, buttercup.
Wake up.

90
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:47,968
[clock chiming]

91
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:57,467
[Boy]
What you got, man?
Anything good?

92
00:06:57,467 --> 00:06:59,467
[Terry]
Watches.

93
00:06:59,467 --> 00:07:02,701
[Boy mutters, chuckles]

94
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:12,367
Oh, Terry!

95
00:07:12,367 --> 00:07:14,334
Come here.
Check this out.

96
00:07:14,334 --> 00:07:16,267
Nice.
I'm keeping this, all right?

97
00:07:16,267 --> 00:07:17,534
Yeah.

98
00:07:33,167 --> 00:07:35,200
[car approaches]

99
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:36,801
[Terry]
Shit!

100
00:07:36,801 --> 00:07:38,334
Let's go.

101
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:48,901
[Boy]
Pop.

102
00:07:51,467 --> 00:07:53,200
Where's my brother?
Forget about him.

103
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:55,167
O'Leary's in
the driveway, man!

104
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:00,133
Cole! Cole!

105
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:02,767
Get up!
Come on, get up!

106
00:08:02,767 --> 00:08:06,100
Cole, pick your feet up!
Come on.

107
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:07,534
Get up!

108
00:08:07,534 --> 00:08:09,234
[door unlocking]

109
00:08:10,701 --> 00:08:13,000
[Man]
Hey! Who the hell is that?

110
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,834
Open the goddamn door!
Come on!

111
00:08:14,834 --> 00:08:16,501
Come on, get up!
Open the door!

112
00:08:16,501 --> 00:08:18,200
[knocking]

113
00:08:20,567 --> 00:08:23,000
Kathleen,
I've brought you something.

114
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,200
Can I come in?

115
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,834
Yeah.

116
00:08:35,701 --> 00:08:39,400
Should call this
"morning, afternoon
and evening" sickness.

117
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:43,234
I know you can't eat it now,
but I made you a sandwich.

118
00:08:43,234 --> 00:08:45,434
It's important you eat.
Oh, God, Ma, get it out.

119
00:08:45,434 --> 00:08:48,067
Peanut butter.
I can smell it.

120
00:08:48,067 --> 00:08:49,567
You need the protein.

121
00:08:49,567 --> 00:08:52,067
I need to feel normal again.

122
00:08:52,067 --> 00:08:54,934
I know. I know.

123
00:09:00,968 --> 00:09:03,934
Does this mean
you're not mad at me?

124
00:09:03,934 --> 00:09:06,901
Don't get
the wrong idea, Katie.

125
00:09:06,901 --> 00:09:11,667
I'm still mad at you
and that boyfriend of yours,

126
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:14,868
but we'll get everything
taken care of.

127
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:19,467
You know what
we discussed, Ma?

128
00:09:20,634 --> 00:09:23,100
It's not such
a terrible thing.

129
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:26,200
No child of mine
is having an abortion.

130
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:59,834
Oh, no.
[dog whines]

131
00:10:03,834 --> 00:10:06,334
[Dad]
No running
in the house!

132
00:10:06,334 --> 00:10:07,767
Kid listens good.

133
00:10:30,901 --> 00:10:34,067
What's with you?
My rabbit.

134
00:10:34,067 --> 00:10:36,801
I forgot to give her
her medicine.

135
00:10:38,334 --> 00:10:39,868
Didn't make it, huh?

136
00:10:41,501 --> 00:10:44,200
Looks like it's gonna be
rabbit fricassee tonight.

137
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:47,400
[chuckles]

138
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:50,400
Why don't you fellas
go on ahead?
I'll meet you later.

139
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:52,734
If I'm late, I want
a 20 on Early Warning.
You got that?

140
00:10:52,734 --> 00:10:54,968
No problemo, Des.
Yeah, I'd hustle if I was you.

141
00:10:54,968 --> 00:10:57,667
There's some good picks
out there today.
Oh, I know it.

142
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:02,367
You think you can get one
past your old man, huh?

143
00:11:02,367 --> 00:11:04,000
[door opens]

144
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,567
What do you mean?
[door closes]

145
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:08,834
When you were crying
like a girl, I smelled
booze on your breath.

146
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:11,067
You can't have it
both ways.

147
00:11:15,667 --> 00:11:17,434
Either you cry like a girl

148
00:11:18,767 --> 00:11:20,567
or you drink like a man.

149
00:11:21,834 --> 00:11:24,100
What's it gonna be?

150
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,801
You think you can drink
like a man at your age,

151
00:11:26,801 --> 00:11:28,534
then follow through
and do it.

152
00:11:29,834 --> 00:11:31,767
As my father used to say,

153
00:11:31,767 --> 00:11:33,701
"Save the tears
for the cemetery

154
00:11:33,701 --> 00:11:35,834
'cause they're wasted
on me."

155
00:11:35,834 --> 00:11:37,467
Go ahead.

156
00:11:39,701 --> 00:11:41,667
Maybe you
shouldn't drink, either.

157
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:44,300
What did you say?

158
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:46,567
Nothing.

159
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:49,501
You know, maybe when I ask you
what I should or shouldn't do,

160
00:11:49,501 --> 00:11:50,968
you'll know you're
old enough to tell me.

161
00:11:57,834 --> 00:11:59,400
Drink.

162
00:12:06,367 --> 00:12:07,667
[spits]

163
00:12:07,667 --> 00:12:09,634
[retching]

164
00:12:13,167 --> 00:12:15,167
Clean up the mess.

165
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:17,767
Any of your friends
want a drink,
you know where to send 'em.

166
00:12:22,167 --> 00:12:24,234
[growling]

167
00:12:24,234 --> 00:12:26,234
Not again.

168
00:12:26,234 --> 00:12:28,534
That's my goddamn shoe.

169
00:12:28,534 --> 00:12:29,801
[growling continues]

170
00:12:31,634 --> 00:12:33,334
Fine.

171
00:12:33,334 --> 00:12:37,234
Didn't fit right, anyway,
you woolly-headed
son of a bitch.

172
00:12:37,234 --> 00:12:40,767
[Priest]
In the name of the Father,
the Son and the Holy Spirit.

173
00:12:40,767 --> 00:12:42,701
[Cole]
Bless me, Father,
for I have sinned.

174
00:12:42,701 --> 00:12:44,968
How long has it been
since your last confession?

175
00:12:44,968 --> 00:12:47,334
My last confession
was about a week a--

176
00:12:47,334 --> 00:12:50,000
a m-month ago.

177
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,934
Go on, young man.

178
00:12:54,234 --> 00:12:56,601
I've had impure thoughts.

179
00:12:57,667 --> 00:13:01,734
I, uh, lied to my mother
a while back,

180
00:13:01,734 --> 00:13:03,067
and my father.

181
00:13:03,067 --> 00:13:04,901
I swore during
the Red Sox game when

182
00:13:04,901 --> 00:13:07,834
Varitek booted the bunt
and they lost.

183
00:13:12,968 --> 00:13:15,434
I got drunk
and robbed a house.

184
00:13:16,767 --> 00:13:18,901
Could you repeat that?

185
00:13:20,968 --> 00:13:22,734
I--

186
00:13:22,734 --> 00:13:25,501
I've had impure thoughts.
No.

187
00:13:25,501 --> 00:13:27,234
The last part.

188
00:13:28,501 --> 00:13:31,300
You mean getting drunk
and robbing-- robbing a house.

189
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:33,100
This is very disturbing, Cole.

190
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,734
You know--

191
00:13:34,734 --> 00:13:37,100
All those Sundays
with you beside me,

192
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:40,567
I should hope
I recognize your voice.

193
00:13:40,567 --> 00:13:43,234
Father, I feel terrible.

194
00:13:43,234 --> 00:13:45,067
My brother
suckered me in.

195
00:13:45,067 --> 00:13:47,834
Terry is not the issue here.

196
00:13:47,834 --> 00:13:50,634
You've gotta be
stronger than that.

197
00:13:51,934 --> 00:13:54,067
There's a lot of bad
in the world,

198
00:13:54,067 --> 00:13:57,767
and it's easy to gravitate
toward the bad.

199
00:13:57,767 --> 00:14:00,100
Be left by the wayside.

200
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:02,200
Do you understand?

201
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:07,267
Yes, Father.
[sighs]

202
00:14:07,267 --> 00:14:11,300
I want you
to think about

203
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:16,767
the clearest, purest thing
that God has given you.

204
00:14:18,434 --> 00:14:21,067
Do you have any idea
what that could be?

205
00:14:21,067 --> 00:14:23,501
Keep you focused.

206
00:14:27,534 --> 00:14:30,067
It's baseball.

207
00:14:30,067 --> 00:14:32,000
Baseball?

208
00:14:33,467 --> 00:14:34,634
[sighs]

209
00:14:34,634 --> 00:14:37,400
What about your plans
to go into the priesthood?

210
00:14:38,968 --> 00:14:41,901
Father, you asked a question.
That's what came out.

211
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:50,033
All you got
is that one pitch.

212
00:14:50,033 --> 00:14:52,367
Sooner or later,
I'm gonna catch up to it.

213
00:14:54,033 --> 00:14:55,567
Come on.

214
00:15:03,968 --> 00:15:07,000
Let me see it.
Let me see it.

215
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:14,133
[clatter, cat yowls]
That was our only ball.

216
00:15:14,133 --> 00:15:16,067
[Woman] Hey!
What are you looking at?

217
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:18,534
You old hagged-up bitch!
Watch your mouth!

218
00:15:18,534 --> 00:15:21,534
[window closes]
I guess the game's over, then.

219
00:15:21,534 --> 00:15:23,501
Cole, don't think you're
anything special, okay?

220
00:15:23,501 --> 00:15:25,367
When it's a money pitch,
I can throw like that, too.

221
00:15:26,434 --> 00:15:28,267
All right, Terry.

222
00:15:30,834 --> 00:15:32,767
Don't be late tonight.

223
00:15:32,767 --> 00:15:35,567
It's Kathleen's
going-away dinner.

224
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:37,667
Good hitting.
Yeah, you, too.

225
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:48,667
Mmm. Smells good.

226
00:15:48,667 --> 00:15:50,334
Fancy dishes.

227
00:15:50,334 --> 00:15:53,701
It's the good china.
From your mother, remember?

228
00:15:53,701 --> 00:15:56,968
[chuckles]
Haven't seen these
in a lifetime.

229
00:15:56,968 --> 00:15:59,701
You kids were in diapers
when I saw these last.

230
00:15:59,701 --> 00:16:01,901
You kids were all
beautiful children.

231
00:16:01,901 --> 00:16:03,434
Weren't they?
[Father chuckles]

232
00:16:03,434 --> 00:16:04,968
They were.

233
00:16:04,968 --> 00:16:06,901
Even Terry.
[laughs]

234
00:16:06,901 --> 00:16:08,767
Terry? No way.
Yeah.

235
00:16:10,067 --> 00:16:11,501
Where is he?

236
00:16:13,901 --> 00:16:16,801
I think I saw him outside
with Anthony.

237
00:16:16,801 --> 00:16:19,901
Ah, the brain trust.
Go get him, will ya?

238
00:16:19,901 --> 00:16:22,200
It's your sister's
going-away dinner.

239
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,901
It's okay.
I'll go get him.

240
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:27,734
[clears throat]

241
00:16:29,534 --> 00:16:31,467
It ain't fair.

242
00:16:31,467 --> 00:16:34,100
The whole ball of wax
ain't fair.

243
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:36,467
There's going to be
another adjustment as well.

244
00:16:36,467 --> 00:16:38,100
Concerns you.

245
00:16:39,601 --> 00:16:41,834
Adjustment?

246
00:16:41,834 --> 00:16:44,033
In order to pay
for your sister,
we're taking you

247
00:16:44,033 --> 00:16:46,467
out of St. Mark's,
putting you in public.

248
00:16:48,334 --> 00:16:49,801
[Cole sighs]

249
00:16:51,501 --> 00:16:53,167
That's Terry's school.

250
00:16:53,167 --> 00:16:55,400
I don't want an argument
out of you.

251
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:56,901
I'll make do.

252
00:16:56,901 --> 00:16:58,868
Raiders are the best team
in the city.

253
00:16:58,868 --> 00:17:00,868
I won't even
make that lineup.

254
00:17:00,868 --> 00:17:02,868
And Father Magruder said
I have a good shot at being

255
00:17:02,868 --> 00:17:04,534
