753
00:52:11,934 --> 00:52:13,367
Come on.

754
00:52:16,801 --> 00:52:19,667
Sorry about the mess.
Don't worry about it.

755
00:52:32,234 --> 00:52:35,534
What's the matter, doc?
Seen a ghost?

756
00:52:38,567 --> 00:52:41,400
I'm afraid the
news isn't good,
Mr. McKay.

757
00:52:41,400 --> 00:52:44,334
The latest MRI
shows it's spreading.

758
00:52:46,300 --> 00:52:48,300
How long we talking?

759
00:52:48,300 --> 00:52:50,501
Well, it's hard
to say.

760
00:52:53,968 --> 00:52:55,501
Have you put your
affairs in order?

761
00:52:57,501 --> 00:53:01,200
My affairs?
Oh sure, doc, sure.

762
00:53:01,200 --> 00:53:04,567
Taxes are all paid up,
college funds set up
for all the kids,

763
00:53:04,567 --> 00:53:06,234
Margaret, she's the
beneficiary in a huge

764
00:53:06,234 --> 00:53:08,601
insurance policy I've
been contributing to

765
00:53:08,601 --> 00:53:10,534
since day one.
Everything's
squared away.

766
00:53:13,701 --> 00:53:16,300
You given any
consideration to
quitting drinking?

767
00:53:16,300 --> 00:53:21,367
Why? So when I'm putting my
affairs in order I can see
how fucked up they are?

768
00:53:26,267 --> 00:53:30,033
Look, I'm sorry, you're
just doing your job.

769
00:53:30,033 --> 00:53:32,133
I kinda knew what
the news was gonna be.

770
00:53:32,133 --> 00:53:35,067
Half my family is underground
by the time they're 40.

771
00:53:37,868 --> 00:53:41,334
I'm trying to think
what I should do.

772
00:53:41,334 --> 00:53:46,701
As a last hurrah. There's a
lot of stuff I haven't done.

773
00:53:46,701 --> 00:53:49,968
Never caught a foul
ball at Fenway.

774
00:53:49,968 --> 00:53:52,968
Never swam in the ocean,
y'know. It's right there,
for Christ's sake.

775
00:53:56,400 --> 00:54:00,400
I can't figure out what
to do. How the hell do
you wrap things up?

776
00:54:01,801 --> 00:54:03,300
You haven't told anyone?

777
00:54:07,033 --> 00:54:09,901
You need to share
this with your family.

778
00:54:16,400 --> 00:54:17,767
Right.

779
00:54:20,234 --> 00:54:22,033
Same stuff as
last time.

780
00:54:22,033 --> 00:54:23,834
Gimme a call.

781
00:54:25,601 --> 00:54:27,100
Here.

782
00:54:32,100 --> 00:54:33,501
[sports chatter]

783
00:54:40,834 --> 00:54:43,033
[sports chatter]

784
00:54:57,767 --> 00:54:59,634
Safe!

785
00:54:59,634 --> 00:55:01,501
[Umpire]
Time out! Time out!
[groaning]

786
00:55:03,601 --> 00:55:05,133
Okay, okay.

787
00:55:05,133 --> 00:55:06,801
Come on. Can you
get up?

788
00:55:13,334 --> 00:55:16,434
Smitty!
That was
intentional, blue!

789
00:55:17,567 --> 00:55:19,701
[sports chatter]

790
00:55:19,701 --> 00:55:21,868
[Umpire]
All right, batter up!

791
00:55:21,868 --> 00:55:23,534
Hold up!

792
00:55:31,033 --> 00:55:32,434
Play ball!

793
00:55:40,033 --> 00:55:42,000
Ball.

794
00:55:42,000 --> 00:55:45,167
[Man]
Hey! Watch your
pitcher over there!

795
00:56:02,467 --> 00:56:04,100
[crowd noise]

796
00:56:32,334 --> 00:56:35,000
Told ya I'd get in
the game one day!

797
00:56:41,033 --> 00:56:43,434
[chatter]

798
00:56:47,767 --> 00:56:51,133
[dishes clatter]

799
00:56:59,868 --> 00:57:02,467
You look great, Katie.

800
00:57:02,467 --> 00:57:05,334
Really, you do.

801
00:57:05,334 --> 00:57:08,200
Do you have any idea
how long I've been
looking for you?

802
00:57:08,200 --> 00:57:10,300
For about as long
as I've been hiding.

803
00:57:17,234 --> 00:57:18,734
Can we talk?

804
00:57:24,434 --> 00:57:25,601
Manny, I
need a break.

805
00:57:25,601 --> 00:57:26,534
Take five.

806
00:57:36,834 --> 00:57:39,300
Have you and David
gotten married?

807
00:57:39,300 --> 00:57:41,467
This? No.

808
00:57:41,467 --> 00:57:45,000
He would never stand
up to his parents
in a million years.

809
00:57:45,000 --> 00:57:47,200
This is so respectable
people such as yourself

810
00:57:47,200 --> 00:57:51,300
don't get the idea that
an unmarried pregnant girl
is serving their eggs.

811
00:57:51,300 --> 00:57:53,601
Slinging eggs and
ham is not the answer.

812
00:57:55,234 --> 00:57:57,100
It just doesn't
make any sense.

813
00:57:57,100 --> 00:58:00,901
Did it make sense to
marry dad when you were
pregnant with Terry?

814
00:58:00,901 --> 00:58:04,300
Thank you, but I'd
rather go it alone
and take my chances.

815
00:58:04,300 --> 00:58:07,868
You think that's why
your father and I
got married?

816
00:58:07,868 --> 00:58:10,067
Don't sit there and tell me
that's not the reason, Ma.

817
00:58:10,067 --> 00:58:11,167
I know that's the reason.

818
00:58:13,734 --> 00:58:15,701
Let me tell
you a story.

819
00:58:15,701 --> 00:58:18,434
I was 22 when
I came to Boston.

820
00:58:18,434 --> 00:58:23,000
I was a beautiful young
woman then and I don't
mind saying so.

821
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:26,567
One night, I met
the most handsome man.

822
00:58:26,567 --> 00:58:30,501
Wonderful dancer, beautiful
singing voice, kind.

823
00:58:30,501 --> 00:58:33,601
He was like no one I'd
ever known before. 

824
00:58:33,601 --> 00:58:38,267
On our first date, we went
to this little Mom n' Pop
Italian place in the North End.

825
00:58:38,267 --> 00:58:43,534
Wherever we went,
someone knew him and
was glad to see him.

826
00:58:45,567 --> 00:58:47,901
He was everything I
was I was looking for.

827
00:58:47,901 --> 00:58:50,100
I gotta get
back inside.
I'm not finished.

828
00:58:52,200 --> 00:58:56,100
Somewhere along
the way your father
stopped being my....

829
00:58:56,100 --> 00:58:57,200
...he just
stopped being.

830
00:58:58,767 --> 00:59:01,734
So I took a job

831
00:59:01,734 --> 00:59:05,100
and raised the family.
Yes, I failed in parts.

832
00:59:06,300 --> 00:59:08,567
But make no mistake,

833
00:59:08,567 --> 00:59:10,968
I gave you
a good start.

834
00:59:10,968 --> 00:59:14,200
Well-spoken and
courteous, you know
how to present yourself

835
00:59:14,200 --> 00:59:16,767
and you didn't get
that from your father.

836
00:59:16,767 --> 00:59:20,133
Everything your father
had to give your
brother Terry took.

837
00:59:20,133 --> 00:59:23,868
He'll pay a price for
it someday, but...

838
00:59:23,868 --> 00:59:27,734
before you decide
on raising this child,

839
00:59:27,734 --> 00:59:31,400
be damned sure you've
got the nerve, not just
the love to raise it,

840
00:59:31,400 --> 00:59:33,300
to go the distance
with that child,

841
00:59:33,300 --> 00:59:35,501
even when nothing else
in your life works.

842
00:59:37,868 --> 00:59:40,734
It takes more than
you know, Kathleen,

843
00:59:40,734 --> 00:59:43,534
and more than
you've got.

844
00:59:51,334 --> 00:59:53,601
What about you?

845
00:59:53,601 --> 00:59:56,567
You stayed in a dead
marriage for years, 
and for what, Ma?

846
00:59:56,567 --> 00:59:59,234
So people would think we
were a normal family?

847
00:59:59,234 --> 01:00:00,701
We're not.
Terry was right.

848
01:00:00,701 --> 01:00:02,300
Terry was not right.

849
01:00:02,300 --> 01:00:06,367
I'll raise this child
to be proud, not ashamed.

850
01:00:06,367 --> 01:00:08,767
He won't be thrown into
some Catholic school
or some seminary

851
01:00:08,767 --> 01:00:10,367
to wipe away the guilt
of his mother.

852
01:00:10,367 --> 01:00:12,834
I won't give up on this baby
like you gave up on Terry.

853
01:00:12,834 --> 01:00:14,734
You take that back!

854
01:00:16,968 --> 01:00:19,801
Does this mean you
won't be coming over
for Christmas or Easter?

855
01:00:29,767 --> 01:00:31,367
McKay!

856
01:00:34,300 --> 01:00:35,300
Coach?

857
01:00:35,300 --> 01:00:36,501
How's the arm feel?

858
01:00:36,501 --> 01:00:39,000
Like it's been
run over.

859
01:00:39,000 --> 01:00:41,200
Graves separated
his shoulder.

860
01:00:41,200 --> 01:00:44,901
That means if we make it
past the semis I'm gonna
need you for the finals, too.

861
01:00:44,901 --> 01:00:46,701
Can you be ready?

862
01:00:46,701 --> 01:00:48,200
I'm ready now.

863
01:00:48,200 --> 01:00:49,534
You sure?

864
01:00:49,534 --> 01:00:51,634
Why wouldn't I be?

865
01:00:55,501 --> 01:00:58,934
Genealogy...you know
what that is?

866
01:01:01,267 --> 01:01:02,834
Yeah.

867
01:01:02,834 --> 01:01:05,767
It's about your
family tree.

868
01:01:05,767 --> 01:01:08,534
Good or bad, you come from
the family you come from.

869
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:13,601
I knew your father,
growing up.

870
01:01:13,601 --> 01:01:17,801
Hell, back then anybody
who knew anything about
baseball heard of him.

871
01:01:17,801 --> 01:01:21,200
He had a gift,

872
01:01:21,200 --> 01:01:24,834
and he just
threw it away.

873
01:01:24,834 --> 01:01:26,767
So let's just say I'm
keeping my eye on you.

874
01:01:38,934 --> 01:01:39,901
Hey.

875
01:01:41,234 --> 01:01:43,000
How did you do today?

876
01:01:43,000 --> 01:01:44,868
You should've been there.
I pitched a good game.

877
01:01:44,868 --> 01:01:47,234
So we win or what?

878
01:01:47,234 --> 01:01:49,133
Yeah, we won.

879
01:01:49,133 --> 01:01:51,634
Good for you.

880
01:01:51,634 --> 01:01:55,701
Maybe if you showed up to
a game once in a while and
actually took an interest

881
01:01:55,701 --> 01:01:57,400
you wouldn't have to ask.

882
01:01:57,400 --> 01:01:59,968
Hey, just because
I wasn't there doesn't
mean I don't care.

883
01:01:59,968 --> 01:02:02,400
I got tied up today,
that's all. How's
the elbow?

884
01:02:02,400 --> 01:02:05,634
That's good.
Keep it iced.

885
01:02:05,634 --> 01:02:08,901
If you're going to pitch 
soon, lay off the breaking
stuff in practice.

886
01:02:08,901 --> 01:02:11,701
Put some ointment on it.
Look dad, honestly,
can we just stop this?

887
01:02:11,701 --> 01:02:13,167
There's no point.

888
01:02:13,167 --> 01:02:15,868
I'm trying to tell
you something--
something important here.

889
01:02:15,868 --> 01:02:18,400
What makes you
advice so good, huh?

890
01:02:20,133 --> 01:02:21,367
Look how far
it got you.

891
01:02:30,167 --> 01:02:33,767
[train whistle blows]
[door slams]

892
01:02:38,467 --> 01:02:43,667
That's right.
Reach out and grab
for your own demise.

893
01:02:43,667 --> 01:02:46,834
Trust me, one more
beer is not going to
make a bit of difference.

894
01:02:48,767 --> 01:02:51,133
Looks like you'll be
joining me, eh, Maggie?

895
01:02:51,133 --> 01:02:54,334
Desmond, we haven't done
anything jointly in years,
this is no time to start.

896
01:02:56,300 --> 01:03:00,033
Yeah, for good reason.

897
01:03:00,033 --> 01:03:03,367
Always gotta keep
knocking me
down, Maggie.

898
01:03:03,367 --> 01:03:06,534
Hold me in contempt
every step of the way.

899
01:03:06,534 --> 01:03:09,801
How did you become the
Queen of Pessimism?

900
01:03:09,801 --> 01:03:11,434
I married the king.

901
01:03:12,667 --> 01:03:14,901
Now we've got a dynasty.

902
01:03:14,901 --> 01:03:19,000
A whole lineage we've passed
on these champion traits to.

903
01:03:19,000 --> 01:03:20,667
Don't start with me,
please. Not tonight.

904
01:03:20,667 --> 01:03:24,567
Big man Desmond McKay.
Big Vietman war hero.

905
01:03:24,567 --> 01:03:27,901
You fight all your battles
in your head.

906
01:03:27,901 --> 01:03:30,000
Leave nothing left
for anyone else.

907
01:03:30,000 --> 01:03:33,200
What do you bring to
this house? Name one thing.

908
01:03:33,200 --> 01:03:34,400
You're stewed,
Maggie.

909
01:03:34,400 --> 01:03:36,300
I deserve to
be stewed.

910
01:03:36,300 --> 01:03:39,100
I'm the only one
who tries to keep
this family together.

911
01:03:39,100 --> 01:03:41,334
Shut up! Shut your trap!

912
01:03:41,334 --> 01:03:42,667
Stop it.

913
01:03:42,667 --> 01:03:45,000
Scram, kid, it's between
your mother and me.

914
01:03:45,000 --> 01:03:48,033
We had all the
promise in the world.
For Chrissake.

915
01:03:48,033 --> 01:03:49,334
That's enough. 
Both of you.

916
01:03:49,334 --> 01:03:51,434
This doesn't concern you!
And now look at you.

917
01:03:51,434 --> 01:03:53,367
How in the world could
I have been so wrong?

918
01:03:53,367 --> 01:03:55,534
Not in front of the boy,
Maggie. I'm warning you.

919
01:03:55,534 --> 01:03:58,400
Or else what? As if
anything you've ever
done has ever mattered.

920
01:03:58,400 --> 01:04:01,167
[dog barking]
Look what you made me do!

921
01:04:01,167 --> 01:04:03,501
That's enough!

922
01:04:03,501 --> 01:04:04,534
[dog barking]

923
01:04:08,601 --> 01:04:09,834
Get out.

924
01:04:30,100 --> 01:04:33,267
[Terry]
I heard Mr. Baseball got his
team in the state finals!

925
01:04:40,968 --> 01:04:43,367
That curve ball is moving
pretty good on you.

926
01:04:45,667 --> 01:04:47,901
Where did you get
the new wheels?

927
01:04:47,901 --> 01:04:49,267
I earned 'em.

928
01:04:53,601 --> 01:04:54,567
Come on.

929
01:04:57,167 --> 01:04:59,267
Would you
lighten up?

930
01:04:59,267 --> 01:05:00,434
Have some of this.

931
01:05:05,033 --> 01:05:07,400
Did you hear about
good old Desmond?

932
01:05:07,400 --> 01:05:10,601
Do I have to?

933
01:05:10,601 --> 01:05:13,534
You're gonna want
to hear this.

934
01:05:13,534 --> 01:05:16,033
He's a dead man.
He's got the big C.

935
01:05:21,067 --> 01:05:23,467
That's bullshit.
He told you?

936
01:05:23,467 --> 01:05:26,834
Everything I needed to know
was in his coat pocket.

937
01:05:26,834 --> 01:05:30,467
He had a pocket
full of these.

938
01:05:30,467 --> 01:05:33,801
I asked Anthony's
uncle, the pharmacist,
what they were.

939
01:05:33,801 --> 01:05:37,033
They give 'em to cancer
patients in the late
stages for the pain.

940
01:05:42,133 --> 01:05:44,634
What's your problem, Terry?

941
01:05:44,634 --> 01:05:47,133
Don't you feel anything?

942
01:05:47,133 --> 01:05:49,868
Yeah.

943
01:05:51,067 --> 01:05:53,334
Relief.

944
01:05:53,334 --> 01:05:54,801
Relief.

945
01:05:56,767 --> 01:05:58,467
Where you going?

946
01:05:59,934 --> 01:06:01,868
I'm through being
out here with you.

947
01:06:01,868 --> 01:06:04,067
Then let's go.

948
01:06:04,067 --> 01:06:06,901
Take the new car
out for a spin.

949
01:06:06,901 --> 01:06:08,100
You don't want me
driving that.

950
01:06:10,067 --> 01:06:11,601
You pitched a good
game today.

951
01:06:11,601 --> 01:06:14,834
You deserve to drive
a real car.

952
01:06:14,834 --> 01:06:17,300
Not like them old fart cars
you park at Marcellino's. 

953
01:06:21,200 --> 01:06:24,133
Oh, I get it. You're
scared to get in
the car with me.

954
01:06:27,067 --> 01:06:29,767
Can you believe I
spent $400 on this?

955
01:06:29,767 --> 01:06:33,000
$400 on a Goddamned
rocket ship.

956
01:06:33,000 --> 01:06:35,968
The guy I bought it from,
he cracked it up about
a month ago,

957
01:06:35,968 --> 01:06:39,100
the frame was all bent,
so I took it to this guy
I know, big meathead.

958
01:06:39,100 --> 01:06:41,100
We did this barter deal.
He fixed it right up. 

959
01:06:41,100 --> 01:06:44,467
Runs pretty good, don't it?
It's got a 350 V-8
engine under the hood.

960
01:06:44,467 --> 01:06:46,667
Said he did some shit to
the engine and the exhaust.

961
01:06:46,667 --> 01:06:49,300
That gearhead shit
goes in one ear and
right out the other.

962
01:06:49,300 --> 01:06:53,701
 <i>** [hard rock, on radio]</i>

963
01:06:53,701 --> 01:06:55,133
What's the matter
with you, bro?

964
01:06:55,133 --> 01:06:56,767
I'm talking to you.

965
01:06:56,767 --> 01:06:58,934
Hey, what's wrong
with you?

966
01:06:58,934 --> 01:07:00,501
[engine revs]

967
01:07:00,501 --> 01:07:04,734
[Terry]
Slow down a little,
I just got this!

968
01:07:04,734 --> 01:07:06,868
[Terry]
Hey! Jesus, what
are you doing?

969
01:07:06,868 --> 01:07:08,667
Hey! Wake up!

970
01:07:08,667 --> 01:07:11,834
[crashing]

971
01:07:11,834 --> 01:07:16,834
[horn blaring]

972
01:07:16,834 --> 01:07:18,567
[dogs barking]

973
01:07:18,567 --> 01:07:22,734
[horn continues blaring]

974
01:07:22,734 --> 01:07:24,801
[horn stops]

975
01:07:37,667 --> 01:07:38,734
Terry!

976
01:07:40,501 --> 01:07:42,634
[Terry gasps]

977
01:07:44,534 --> 01:07:46,133
Get out and push.

978
01:07:50,067 --> 01:07:52,467
You totaled my car.

979
01:07:52,467 --> 01:07:53,968
I'll make it up to you.

980
01:07:56,067 --> 01:07:58,300
Terry, you still bleeding?
You're still bleeding.

981
01:08:00,067 --> 01:08:01,534
Get off!

982
01:08:03,133 --> 01:08:05,601
[police siren wails]

983
01:08:08,033 --> 01:08:09,968
Where do you boys think
you're going?

984
01:08:13,267 --> 01:08:15,334
Probably to jail.

985
01:08:15,334 --> 01:08:20,100
[phone rings]
 <i>[baseball game on TV]</i>

986
01:08:20,100 --> 01:08:25,400
[phone rings]

987
01:08:25,400 --> 01:08:27,367
[Desmond]
Hello?

988
01:08:27,367 --> 01:08:30,133
Yeah.

989
01:08:30,133 --> 01:08:32,033
Yeah.

990
01:08:36,067 --> 01:08:38,601
You're where?

991
01:08:45,634 --> 01:08:50,200
Let 'em think
it over for the night.

992
01:08:50,200 --> 01:08:52,100
[sighs]

993
01:09:10,000 --> 01:09:12,000
So, how much
trouble is he in?

994
01:09:12,000 --> 01:09:13,601
Basically none.

995
01:09:13,601 --> 01:09:15,667
You got
a good kid here.

996
01:09:15,667 --> 01:09:16,701
Good pitcher, too.

997
01:09:16,701 --> 01:09:20,868
My kid's on the same team.

998
01:09:20,868 --> 01:09:23,234
I'd like to see them go
all the way this year.

999
01:09:23,234 --> 01:09:24,467
Where's your brother?

1000
01:09:24,467 --> 01:09:26,534
He was released on his
own recognizance

1001
01:09:26,534 --> 01:09:28,501
because he's old enough.

1002
01:09:28,501 --> 01:09:30,100
We couldn't let this
one leave on his own.

1003
01:09:30,100 --> 01:09:32,100
So isn't there something
you can charge him with?

1004
01:09:32,100 --> 01:09:33,334
Excuse me?

1005
01:09:33,334 --> 01:09:34,934
Nothing too serious.

1006
01:09:34,934 --> 01:09:38,334
I come down all this way,
it shouldn't be for nothing.

1007
01:09:38,334 --> 01:09:40,601
Consider this your kid's
lucky day, Mr. McKay.

1008
01:09:40,601 --> 01:09:42,934
I mean,
no one got hurt.

1009
01:09:42,934 --> 01:09:44,734
We're gonna cut
him a little slack.

1010
01:09:44,734 --> 01:09:46,334
Yeah, well, somebody
gotta teach him a lesson.

1011
01:09:46,334 --> 01:09:49,100
So is it going to be you guys
who should be doing their jobs

1012
01:09:49,100 --> 01:09:51,133
instead of feeding my kid
doughnuts, or me?

1013
01:09:51,133 --> 01:09:52,133
Dad, they said we can go.

1014
01:09:52,133 --> 01:09:53,133
I heard what he said.

1015
01:09:53,133 --> 01:09:54,934
Move!

1016
01:09:59,133 --> 01:10:00,200
Mr. McKay?

1017
01:10:00,200 --> 01:10:01,601
[Officer]
Take it easy on him.

1018
01:10:01,601 --> 01:10:04,000
You don't want to wind up
with two Terrys on your hands.

1019
01:10:04,000 --> 01:10:05,100
Yeah, sure.

1020
01:10:05,100 --> 01:10:07,234
Thanks for the
profound insight.

1021
01:10:14,067 --> 01:10:15,901
Put your seatbelt on.

1022
01:10:20,934 --> 01:10:25,300
Don't you ever, ever
humiliate me like that again!

1023
01:10:25,300 --> 01:10:27,467
You understand me?

1024
01:10:28,634 --> 01:10:32,067
I'm sorry.

1025
01:10:32,067 --> 01:10:33,934
You should know better than
to get in a car with Terry.

1026
01:10:33,934 --> 01:10:36,234
What's the matter with you?

1027
01:10:36,234 --> 01:10:37,901
Terry wasn't driving,
Dad, I was.

1028
01:10:37,901 --> 01:10:40,067
Don't pull
that crap on me.

1029
01:10:42,801 --> 01:10:44,534
Forget about Terry.

1030
01:10:44,534 --> 01:10:50,067
Terry is beyond--

1031
01:10:50,067 --> 01:10:51,934
You I can
do something about.

1032
01:10:51,934 --> 01:10:54,434
You and me, we're
gonna go back home

1033
01:10:54,434 --> 01:10:57,467
and catch
the doubleheader.

1034
01:10:57,467 --> 01:10:58,501
[keys jingling]

1035
01:11:14,801 --> 01:11:17,234
[Man]
Right. Hey, listen,
let me call you back.

1036
01:11:17,234 --> 01:11:19,434
Someone just came in.

1037
01:11:19,434 --> 01:11:20,434
Can I help you?

1038
01:11:20,434 --> 01:11:22,334
Yes, sir.

1039
01:11:22,334 --> 01:11:24,634
I've thought about this.

1040
01:11:24,634 --> 01:11:26,567
I want to sign up.

1041
01:11:26,567 --> 01:11:27,467
Serve my country.

1042
01:11:27,467 --> 01:11:29,367
Please, have a seat.

1043
01:11:37,033 --> 01:11:39,167
I know you.
You're a local kid, right?

1044
01:11:39,167 --> 01:11:40,400
McKay?

1045
01:11:40,400 --> 01:11:41,267
Terry McKay.

1046
01:11:45,968 --> 01:11:47,601
Son, do you know
the Marine Corps motto?

1047
01:11:47,601 --> 01:11:49,200
Yes, sir.

1048
01:11:49,200 --> 01:11:50,567
 <i>Semper fi.</i>

1049
01:11:50,567 --> 01:11:52,367
Yes, there's that.

1050
01:11:52,367 --> 01:11:56,033
There's also the few,
the proud, the Marines.

1051
01:11:56,033 --> 01:11:57,100
Right.

1052
01:11:57,100 --> 01:12:00,501
With an emphasis
on the few,

1053
01:12:00,501 --> 01:12:02,901
which means we're
very selective.

1054
01:12:02,901 --> 01:12:04,434
You're not even out
of high school yet

1055
01:12:04,434 --> 01:12:06,567
and you've already
got a criminal record.

1056
01:12:06,567 --> 01:12:09,501
Son, I don't think you're
Marine Corps material.

1057
01:12:10,734 --> 01:12:14,334
It's got to be the Marines.

1058
01:12:14,334 --> 01:12:16,834
I'm sorry, son.
I can't help you.

1059
01:12:25,767 --> 01:12:28,567
You guys are
a bunch of pussies.

1060
01:12:39,200 --> 01:12:40,567
 <i>[crowd cheering]</i>

1061
01:12:40,567 --> 01:12:43,467
 <i>[Announcer]</i>
 <i>Right field.</i>
 <i>Hit deep.</i>

1062
01:12:43,467 --> 01:12:44,434
 <i>Nixon on the run.</i>

1063
01:12:44,434 --> 01:12:45,567
[beer can opening]

1064
01:12:45,567 --> 01:12:47,033
Right down the middle.

1065
01:12:47,033 --> 01:12:48,434
 <i>[Announcer]</i>
 <i>It's gone.</i>

1066
01:12:48,434 --> 01:12:51,701
Should have never pulled
Wakefield, you stupid bastards.

1067
01:12:51,701 --> 01:12:53,968
You want me
to turn it off?

1068
01:12:53,968 --> 01:12:56,367
Don't you dare.

1069
01:12:56,367 --> 01:12:58,367
Let's see how that
son of a bitch does.

1070
01:13:01,133 --> 01:13:03,267
You know what I like
about this game?

1071
01:13:05,667 --> 01:13:09,367
Baseball is exactly
like life.

1072
01:13:09,367 --> 01:13:15,334
The majority of the time,
absolutely nothing happens.

1073
01:13:15,334 --> 01:13:18,267
Then certain moments
and certain days,

1074
01:13:18,267 --> 01:13:20,033
you get all the
glory in the world,

1075
01:13:20,033 --> 01:13:21,067
or all the shit.

1076
01:13:25,067 --> 01:13:27,534
You caught a break today,
you know that, don't you?

1077
01:13:27,534 --> 01:13:29,200
Yeah.

1078
01:13:29,200 --> 01:13:30,634
You don't get too many.

1079
01:13:39,100 --> 01:13:42,801
You should come out
and see me pitch, Dad.

1080
01:13:42,801 --> 01:13:44,133
I'm doing really good.

1081
01:13:46,334 --> 01:13:49,100
We made it to state final.

1082
01:13:49,100 --> 01:13:52,534
You don't want me to start
turning up now, kid.

1083
01:13:52,534 --> 01:13:54,400
You got a streak going,
you go with it.

1084
01:13:54,400 --> 01:13:56,267
Don't change a thing.

1085
01:14:05,167 --> 01:14:07,968
Did you ever catch one?

1086
01:14:07,968 --> 01:14:10,200
A break?

1087
01:14:10,200 --> 01:14:13,734
Eh, a few
here and there.

1088
01:14:13,734 --> 01:14:17,300
Some people, life
just happens to them.

1089
01:14:17,300 --> 01:14:22,400
Don't put yourself
in the position where
you have no choice.

1090
01:14:22,400 --> 01:14:25,501
Only choice I ever made
was marrying your mother.

1091
01:14:25,501 --> 01:14:28,100
You see how that
turned out.

1092
01:14:30,801 --> 01:14:34,367
Nah.

1093
01:14:34,367 --> 01:14:37,100
I loved your mother.

1094
01:15:04,767 --> 01:15:06,434
Sorry I'm late, Joey.

1095
01:15:06,434 --> 01:15:08,534
Had to take care
of something at home.

1096
01:15:08,534 --> 01:15:09,767
Start in the dining room,

1097
01:15:09,767 --> 01:15:11,901
then I'm going to need
help with the cars.

1098
01:15:11,901 --> 01:15:13,467
Don't forget, you're closing
up with me tonight.

1099
01:15:13,467 --> 01:15:14,467
Right, yeah.

1100
01:15:14,467 --> 01:15:15,467
One more thing.

1101
01:15:15,467 --> 01:15:16,767
Congratulations.

1102
01:15:16,767 --> 01:15:18,634
I heard you made
it into the finals.

1103
01:15:18,634 --> 01:15:19,901
Yeah, thanks.

1104
01:15:19,901 --> 01:15:21,400
Maybe when you make
it into the majors,

1105
01:15:21,400 --> 01:15:22,701
you can wear
a Marcellino's patch

1106
01:15:22,701 --> 01:15:24,601
on your sleeve or something.

1107
01:15:24,601 --> 01:15:28,334
Hup!
What do we got?

1108
01:15:28,334 --> 01:15:30,601
Here we go.

1109
01:15:33,000 --> 01:15:35,868
 <i>[Announcer]</i>
 <i>This part of the organization</i>
 <i>welcomes these guys back.</i>

1110
01:15:35,868 --> 01:15:38,367
 <i>Right down the right</i>
 <i>field line, that's trouble!</i>

1111
01:15:38,367 --> 01:15:39,701
 <i>Sheffield in the corner.</i>

1112
01:15:39,701 --> 01:15:42,534
 <i>A fair ball and a home run!</i>

1113
01:15:42,534 --> 01:15:43,501
 <i>Home run,</i>
 <i>Manny Ramirez!</i>

1114
01:15:43,501 --> 01:15:44,901
 <i>Still running hard.</i>

1115
01:15:44,901 --> 01:15:48,634
 <i>Three to nothing,</i>
 <i>Boston, in the first.</i>

1116
01:15:48,634 --> 01:15:51,334
 <i>I think they have</i>
 <i>arsenal right here.</i>

1117
01:15:51,334 --> 01:15:52,601
 <i>Posada is saying--</i>

1118
01:15:52,601 --> 01:15:56,100
Yeah!

1119
01:15:56,100 --> 01:15:58,834
 <i>[Announcer]</i>
 <i>Posada running down</i>
 <i>the right field line.</i>

1120
01:15:58,834 --> 01:16:03,767
 <i>Derek Jeter, team captain,</i>
 <i>verging towards--</i>

1121
01:16:03,767 --> 01:16:05,300
[table crashing]

1122
01:16:05,300 --> 01:16:08,167
Fuck!

1123
01:16:08,167 --> 01:16:10,801
 <i>[Announcer]</i>
 <i>You can see it again</i>
 <i>on the replay.</i>

1124
01:16:10,801 --> 01:16:13,601
 <i>It appeared from here</i>
 <i>that although the ball</i>

1125
01:16:13,601 --> 01:16:17,300
 <i>was hooking, it was just</i>
 <i>inside the foul pole.</i>

1126
01:16:23,234 --> 01:16:24,901
Hey, Cole?

1127
01:16:24,901 --> 01:16:26,501
How about giving me
a hand with these, huh?

1128
01:16:26,501 --> 01:16:28,734
I gotta hit the stock room.

1129
01:16:28,734 --> 01:16:31,133
No problem, Joey.

1130
01:16:33,234 --> 01:16:39,100
 <i>[Announcer on TV]</i>
 <i>It comes with all this,</i>
 <i>no-risk money-back guarentee.</i>

1131
01:16:40,434 --> 01:16:43,567
Desmond?

1132
01:16:43,567 --> 01:16:46,467
 <i>[Announcer on TV]</i>
 <i>...cigarette smoke,</i>
 <i>animal dander and--</i>

1133
01:16:50,734 --> 01:16:54,067
[door opening]

1134
01:16:54,067 --> 01:16:55,701
[door closing]

1135
01:16:55,701 --> 01:16:57,033
We're closed.

1136
01:16:57,033 --> 01:16:59,467
No shit.

1137
01:16:59,467 --> 01:17:01,067
You owe me.

1138
01:17:01,067 --> 01:17:02,400
Terry,
get out of here.

1139
01:17:02,400 --> 01:17:03,801
This isn't my money.

1140
01:17:03,801 --> 01:17:05,801
You know who owns this place.
Are you crazy?

1141
01:17:05,801 --> 01:17:07,334
Makes no difference
to me who owns it.

1142
01:17:07,334 --> 01:17:08,400
It should.

1143
01:17:09,767 --> 01:17:11,601
I said I'll make
it up to you.

1144
01:17:14,868 --> 01:17:18,868
All you gotta do is shut
up and open the register.

1145
01:17:18,868 --> 01:17:20,234
Just get out of here.

1146
01:17:20,234 --> 01:17:23,000
[cocking gun]
Open it.

1147
01:17:24,767 --> 01:17:26,767
Anthony, don't point
that thing at my brother,
you hear me?

1148
01:17:26,767 --> 01:17:28,167
Shut up!

1149
01:17:30,934 --> 01:17:32,000
Drop the gun.

1150
01:17:36,634 --> 01:17:39,100
[Joey groaning]

1151
01:17:40,868 --> 01:17:42,467
Is this your place,
you bastard?

1152
01:17:42,467 --> 01:17:44,467
Both of yous are dead,
you hear?

1153
01:17:44,467 --> 01:17:47,767
Yeah, well, what if
I kill you first, huh?

1154
01:17:47,767 --> 01:17:49,234
Then, how are you
gonna pay us back?

1155
01:17:49,234 --> 01:17:50,868
Hey, genius.

1156
01:17:50,868 --> 01:17:53,267
What do you think, I'm some
lone fucking wolf here?

1157
01:17:53,267 --> 01:17:55,734
I got plenty of friends that'd
enjoy looking for yous,

1158
01:17:55,734 --> 01:17:57,767
especially if I were dead.

1159
01:17:59,534 --> 01:18:01,000
Well, then I guess
I got no choice, huh?

1160
01:18:01,000 --> 01:18:03,534
Anthony, don't!

1161
01:18:03,534 --> 01:18:05,334
Jesus Christ!

1162
01:18:08,901 --> 01:18:10,000
Hey, Cole,

1163
01:18:10,000 --> 01:18:11,367
this one's your
brother, right?

1164
01:18:11,367 --> 01:18:14,701
Obviously he didn't get
the brains in the family.

1165
01:18:14,701 --> 01:18:16,067
At least I know
how to find you.

1166
01:18:16,067 --> 01:18:17,834
Shut up!
I still got the gun!

1167
01:18:17,834 --> 01:18:20,267
Open the goddamn drawer!

1168
01:18:20,267 --> 01:18:21,534
You open it yourself,

1169
01:18:21,534 --> 01:18:23,901
I'm not going to help
you dig your own grave.

1170
01:18:26,000 --> 01:18:27,200
It's for Dad, Cole.

1171
01:18:27,200 --> 01:18:29,801
The money's for Dad,
all right?

1172
01:18:29,801 --> 01:18:32,100
No amount of money is going
to make Dad better, Terry.

1173
01:18:33,801 --> 01:18:35,601
Hey, Cole.

1174
01:18:35,601 --> 01:18:38,033
You better call me an
ambulance, I'm bleeding
like a son of a bitch.

1175
01:18:38,033 --> 01:18:40,234
No one's using the phone!

1176
01:18:45,701 --> 01:18:48,067
Make sure he gets
taken care of.

1177
01:18:48,067 --> 01:18:50,300
Hey, Cole,
one more thing.

1178
01:18:50,300 --> 01:18:52,000
Only this guy robbed us.

1179
01:18:52,000 --> 01:18:54,334
Your idiot brother had nothing
to do with it, understand?

1180
01:18:54,334 --> 01:18:57,467
No, Joey, no way, I'll say
he was here if I have to.

1181
01:18:57,467 --> 01:18:58,467
You little narc!

1182
01:18:58,467 --> 01:18:59,801
Hey, asshole?

1183
01:18:59,801 --> 01:19:02,667
This little narc's trying
to keep you breathing.

1184
01:19:02,667 --> 01:19:06,234
You know why I don't
want you here, tough guy?

1185
01:19:06,234 --> 01:19:08,200
I'll tell you why.

1186
01:19:08,200 --> 01:19:10,434
So when they find you dead,
the cops won't make
a connection

1187
01:19:10,434 --> 01:19:12,434
between you and me,
you junkie piece of shit.

1188
01:19:12,434 --> 01:19:13,300
Shut up!

1189
01:19:13,300 --> 01:19:14,200
Fuck you!

1190
01:19:14,200 --> 01:19:15,901
Don't you tell me
to shut up!

1191
01:19:15,901 --> 01:19:17,767
[cocking gun]
Terry!

1192
01:19:17,767 --> 01:19:18,868
Don't.

1193
01:19:26,434 --> 01:19:29,901
You can't shoot me.

1194
01:19:29,901 --> 01:19:31,167
We're family.

1195
01:19:32,601 --> 01:19:36,167
You and me.

1196
01:19:36,167 --> 01:19:40,601
Black Irish.

1197
01:19:40,601 --> 01:19:44,400
You're more like
black licorice.

1198
01:19:44,400 --> 01:19:48,501
You're soft and sweet.

1199
01:19:48,501 --> 01:19:50,968
You're hollow
on the inside.

1200
01:19:50,968 --> 01:19:54,000
We may be brothers,
but I'm nothing like you.

1201
01:19:59,567 --> 01:20:01,968
You got that right.

1202
01:20:01,968 --> 01:20:03,367
[gun cocking]

1203
01:20:03,367 --> 01:20:04,701
[gun fires]

1204
01:20:17,267 --> 01:20:19,200
 <i>[police radio chatter]</i>

1205
01:20:23,200 --> 01:20:25,501
Come on, son.

1206
01:20:28,067 --> 01:20:30,400
[hanging up phone]

1207
01:20:30,400 --> 01:20:32,400
Can I go now, please?

1208
01:20:32,400 --> 01:20:34,000
I'll take you over
to the hospital.

1209
01:20:59,534 --> 01:21:01,634
[EKG beeping]

1210
01:21:07,734 --> 01:21:08,968
I'm sorry.

1211
01:21:08,968 --> 01:21:09,968
Aw.

1212
01:21:09,968 --> 01:21:11,067
I had no choice.

1213
01:21:11,067 --> 01:21:13,234
Of course
you didn't.

1214
01:21:13,234 --> 01:21:14,901
I'm glad you're here.

1215
01:21:14,901 --> 01:21:17,601
You go see your father.

1216
01:21:17,601 --> 01:21:19,534
[EKG beeping]

1217
01:21:35,167 --> 01:21:36,167
McKay.

1218
01:21:36,167 --> 01:21:38,100
Go ahead.

1219
01:22:00,400 --> 01:22:02,367
[chair dragging]

1220
01:22:16,968 --> 01:22:18,901
[whispers]
Our Father,

1221
01:22:18,901 --> 01:22:22,067
who art in heaven,

1222
01:22:22,067 --> 01:22:23,400
hallow--

1223
01:22:26,667 --> 01:22:29,234
Hallowed be thy--

1224
01:22:33,167 --> 01:22:36,834
Hallowed be--

1225
01:22:38,634 --> 01:22:40,901
[sniffing]

1226
01:22:49,400 --> 01:22:52,434
[sniffing]

1227
01:22:53,968 --> 01:22:56,868
Jesus, Terry,
why'd you make me do it?

1228
01:22:59,601 --> 01:23:04,501
[rain pelting window]

1229
01:24:17,501 --> 01:24:20,934
What are you looking at?

1230
01:24:25,367 --> 01:24:30,133
Doesn't look too
bad up there.

1231
01:24:30,133 --> 01:24:33,734
Hell no,
it looks peaceful.

1232
01:24:33,734 --> 01:24:37,100
Nice and quiet.

1233
01:24:37,100 --> 01:24:40,200
No disappointed wife.

1234
01:24:40,200 --> 01:24:44,033
No kids driving
you up the wall.

1235
01:24:44,033 --> 01:24:47,133
People admire you.

1236
01:24:47,133 --> 01:24:50,400
How about we switch, huh?

1237
01:24:50,400 --> 01:24:52,267
I'll go up there
on the cross,

1238
01:24:52,267 --> 01:24:54,501
you come down here
and live in South Boston.

1239
01:24:54,501 --> 01:24:56,601
Ahem.

1240
01:25:00,667 --> 01:25:03,000
How long you been here?

1241
01:25:03,000 --> 01:25:05,234
Since last night.

1242
01:25:06,501 --> 01:25:09,567
Grab those clothes
there, would you?

1243
01:25:09,567 --> 01:25:12,534
[clearing his throat]

1244
01:25:12,534 --> 01:25:14,701
[coughing]

1245
01:25:19,501 --> 01:25:24,067
Nah, that's not such
a good idea, Dad.

1246
01:25:24,067 --> 01:25:27,634
